\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":100},\"unstrip-depth\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":20},\"unstrip-size\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":5000000},\"timingprofile\":[\"100.00%    6.496      1 -total\",\" 71.57%    4.649      1 Template:Variant-343\",\" 52.66%    3.421      1 Template:Version_icon\",\" 31.99%    2.078      1 Template:Top_icon\",\" 25.19%    1.636      2 Template:Frac\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240926182825\",\"ttl\":604800,\"transientcontent\":false}}});mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":55});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"'''Clear thoughts''' is a [[property]] that appears in [[dNetHack]], [[notdNetHack]] and [[notnotdNetHack]].\n\n==Description== \nA character with clear thoughts has their [[sanity]] always treated as the maximum of 100 for any effects that check their sanity level. As a result, both chance-based and guaranteed madness effects are entirely ignored or suppressed, and a character will never suffer the negative effects of suddenly losing sanity, such as [[screaming]] or panicking: this does not affect their actual sanity level, which will continue to rise or drop as normal, and madnesses can still be gained, but are also suppressed like other pre-existing madnesses.\n\nIf a character loses clear thoughts, the effects of their madnesses will immediately resume as normal.\n\n===Sources===\nThe following objects confer clear thoughts:\n\n* [[DNetHack artifacts#Spear of Peace|The Spear of Peace]], extrinsically while carried\n* [[The Star of Hypernotus]], extrinsically while carried\n* A [[Insight#Living doll merchants|doll of clear thinking]], intrinsically for 100 turns when [[applied]] \n\n===Walking nightmare===\nIf a character has both the walking nightmare property and the clear thoughts property, the clear thoughts property is partially blocked and the effects of losing sanity are no longer suppressed. The character's sanity loss is treated as {{frac|5}} of its current value, with every 5 points of sanity loss corresponding to one point while afflicted by nightmares (e.g., 0 normal sanity is 80 effective sanity). The effects of sanity loss scale with this lowered sanity loss, and last for only {{frac|5}} of their normal duration.\n\nCurrently, the only source of the walking nightmare property is [[the War-helm of the Dreaming]].\n\n==Strategy==\nHold on to an extrinsic source of clear thoughts as tightly as possible - losing clear thoughts while at low normal sanity is very dangerous.\n{{variant-343}}\n[[Category:dNetHack properties]]\n[[Category:notdNetHack properties]]\n[[Category:notnotdNetHack properties]]"}